snippet: Roberto Bautista Agut won the singles title in Auckland, New Zealand, when Sock was forced to retire while trailing, 6-1, 1-0.
abstract: Roberto Bautista Agut wins ASB Classic singles title after Jack Sock quits match due to illness; other tennis news noted.
lead_paragraph: Roberto Bautista Agut won the singles title in Auckland, New Zealand, when Sock was forced to retire while trailing, 6-1, 1-0.

headline.main: Illness Forces Jack Sock Out of ASB Classic
